# CLI Interfaces

Thin layer only — delegate to use cases in `src/application/use-cases/`.

## Entry

@src/interfaces/cli/agent.controller.ts — Commander commands: `validate-config`, `run`, `inspect`, `report`, `capture-auth`, `preflight`, `read-pr-context`, `pipeline prepare`, `pipeline correlate`.

## Exit codes

@src/interfaces/cli/exit-codes.ts:

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| 0 | OK |
| 1 | Bugs found (HIGH/CRITICAL or FAILED/BLOCKED) |
| 2 | Config error |
| 3 | Harness fatal |
| 4 | Timeout |
| 5 | Onboarding blocked |
| 6 | Pipeline preflight or correlation blocked |

Use `classifyError()`, `classifyResult()`, and `classifyCorrelationResult()` — do not invent new exit codes without updating docs.

## Rules

- No business logic in controller — inject use cases via NestJS DI.
- New command → new use case + register in `APPLICATION_PROVIDERS` and controller.
- Update @doc/17-configuration-and-cli.md when CLI surface changes.
